PHP – Use Cases
PHP is mainly used for server-side web development. Common use cases include:
Dynamic Websites – Create pages that change based on user input
Form Handling – Process login, registration, contact forms
Database Operations – Insert, update, delete, fetch data (MySQL, etc.)
Authentication Systems – Login, signup, password management
Content Management Systems – Blogs, news sites (WordPress)
E-commerce Websites – Product listing, cart, orders, payments
REST APIs – Backend services for web & mobile apps
